article.headline: Boston College 75, Miami 68
article.story: CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) -- Jared Dudley scored 26 points to lead Boston College to a 75-68 victory over Miami on Wednesday night. Dudley scored nine consecutive points in a 2:22 span late in the second half to put the Eagles ahead for good 65-60 with 3:37 remaining in the game. Tyrese Rice secured the victory for the Eagles (17-6, 8-2 Atlantic Coast Conference) with six free throws and a field goal in the final 2:04. Reese finished with 21 points. The roster-depleted Hurricanes, which dressed only seven scholarship players, stayed within striking distance throughout the game. Denis Clemente's 3-pointer with 6:26 remaining tied it 60-60. Clemente led the Hurricanes with 24 points while Jack McClinton added 14. Miami (9-15, 2-8) has now lost seven straight. John Oates scored seven points in a 12-2 run to start the second half which put the Eagles ahead 44-37 with 14:18 remaining in the game. But the Hurricanes responded with a 9-2 run in the next 4:31. Clemente keyed the run with a field goal and 3-pointer. Miami opened to a 15-7 lead in the in the first 6:24. The Eagles ran off nine unanswered points in the next 3:04 to take the lead 16-15. Clemente scored four his first half 14 points on consecutive layups to put the Hurricanes ahead 32-29 with 2:05 remaining in the first half.
